Excellent â€” let's address both your points:

âœ… 1. What is {{ .Release.Name }} in Helm?
{{ .Release.Name }} is a Helm built-in template variable that represents the name of the Helm release you provide during installation:

Example:
helm install fastapi-dev ./charts/fastapi-chart --values charts/fastapi-chart/values-dev.yaml
Here:

{{ .Release.Name }} â†’ becomes fastapi-dev

Used to name resources like the Kubernetes Deployment and Service

âœ… 2. Create Environment-Specific Values Files
We'll create values-dev.yaml, values-uat.yaml, and values-prod.yaml for separate environments.

ğŸ“ charts/fastapi-chart/values-dev.yaml
image:
  repository: <your-acr-name>.azurecr.io/fastapi-app
  tag: dev
  pullPolicy: Always

service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  port: 80

containerPort: 80
replicaCount: 1
ğŸ“ charts/fastapi-chart/values-uat.yaml
image:
  repository: <your-acr-name>.azurecr.io/fastapi-app
  tag: uat
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent

service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  port: 80

containerPort: 80
replicaCount: 2
ğŸ“ charts/fastapi-chart/values-prod.yaml
image:
  repository: <your-acr-name>.azurecr.io/fastapi-app
  tag: prod
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent

service:
  type: LoadBalancer
  port: 80

containerPort: 80
replicaCount: 3
ğŸ› ï¸ Update the Chart to Use replicaCount
ğŸ”„ Update deployment.yaml:
